Key Match Events: Khama Billiat scored the winning penalty for Zimbabwe
Jordan Zemura was fouled inside the box leading to the penalty
Miscellaneous Highlights: Zimbabwe struggled to maintain ball possession, a consistent rhythm and lacked creativeness in the final third
Namibia could have equalised had they been clinical in front of goal
A lackadaisical Warriors side almost doubled the lead through Daniel Msendami whose shot in the second half also hit the upright
Others: Zimbabwe now top Group J with five points
They are one point ahead of Kenya and Cameroon who are second and third respectively but are yet to play each other
Zimbabwe will play Namibia again on Monday in the second leg of the AFCON qualifier
